{
  "analysis": "The repository is in /app/ocaml. It is not configured, and boot/ lacks ocamlrun. The task points to run-length compression of free space in the major heap, likely implemented in runtime/shared_heap.c and related headers. We need to inspect the actual sweep/free-list implementation to identify the broken code before configuring/building to reproduce and fix the crash.",
  "plan": "Search runtime headers and shared_heap.c for sweep/free-list/run-length/pool structures and functions. Inspect the top of shared_heap.c and relevant header definitions to understand the allocator/sweep code. This should reveal the modified run-length free-space logic.",
  "commands": [
    {
      "keystrokes": "ls -la runtime/caml/*.h | sed -n '1,120p'\n",
      "duration": 0.1
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "grep -RinE 'run.length|run_length|runlength|rle|rl_|free_space|free_list|freelist|pool_freelist|sweep|FREE|GARBAGE|free_block|next_free' runtime/shared_heap.c runtime/caml/shared_heap*.h runtime/caml/*.h | sed -n '1,260p'\n",
      "duration": 0.5
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "sed -n '1,260p' runtime/shared_heap.c\n",
      "duration": 0.1
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "sed -n '1,220p' runtime/caml/shared_heap.h 2>/dev/null || grep -RinE 'shared_heap|pool|free|sweep' runtime/caml/*.h | sed -n '1,220p'\n",
      "duration": 0.1
    }
  ]
}
